# PowerShell Setup Guide for YouTube to MP3 Converter

This guide provides step-by-step PowerShell commands to set up and run the YouTube to MP3 Converter on Windows 11.

## 🚀 Quick Setup (PowerShell Commands)

### Step 1: Open PowerShell as Administrator
1. Press `Win + X` and select "Windows PowerShell (Admin)" or "Windows PowerShell (Admin)"
2. If prompted by UAC, click "Yes"

### Step 2: Navigate to Your Projects Directory
```powershell
# Navigate to your documents or preferred directory
Set-Location "$env:USERPROFILE\Documents"
# OR
Set-Location "C:\Projects"
# OR create a new directory
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path "C:\Projects\youtube-to-mp3-converter" -Force
Set-Location "C:\Projects\youtube-to-mp3-converter"
```

### Step 3: Install Python (if not already installed)
```powershell
# Check if Python is installed
python --version

# If not installed, download from: https://www.python.org/downloads/
# Make sure to check "Add Python to PATH" during installation
```

### Step 4: Install FFmpeg

#### Option A: Using Chocolatey (Recommended)
```powershell
# Install Chocolatey if not already installed
Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force
[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072
Invoke-Expression ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))

# Install FFmpeg
choco install ffmpeg -y

# Verify installation
ffmpeg -version
```

#### Option B: Manual Installation
```powershell
# Download FFmpeg from: https://ffmpeg.org/download.html#build-windows
# Extract to C:\ffmpeg

# Add to system PATH
$env:PATH += ";C:\ffmpeg\bin"
[Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("PATH", $env:PATH, "Machine")

# Verify installation (open new PowerShell window)
ffmpeg -version
```

### Step 5: Set Up the Project

```powershell
# Clone the repository (if using Git)
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/youtube-to-mp3-converter.git
Set-Location "youtube-to-mp3-converter"

# OR if you have the source files, copy them to this directory
```

### Step 6: Create Virtual Environment
```powershell
# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate virtual environment
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# You should see (venv) in your prompt
```

**If you get execution policy error:**
```powershell
# Allow script execution
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```

### Step 7: Install Dependencies
```powershell
# Upgrade pip first
python -m pip install --upgrade pip

# Install all required packages
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**If some packages fail to install individually:**
```powershell
# Install core dependencies first
pip install Flask==3.0.0
pip install yt-dlp==2023.12.30
pip install Flask-CORS==4.0.0
pip install python-dotenv==1.0.0
pip install validators==0.22.0
pip install Flask-Limiter==3.5.0
pip install Werkzeug==3.0.1
```

### Step 8: Run the Application
```powershell
# Start the Flask development server
python app.py
```

### Step 9: Access the Application
1. Open your web browser
2. Navigate to: `http://127.0.0.1:5000`
3. You should see the YouTube to MP3 converter interface

